---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ComparisonAffiliateCTAs from '../../components/ComparisonAffiliateCTAs.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  title: 'Relume vs Framer AI',
  description: 'Relume vs Framer: Which AI website builder is better? Compare Webflow components vs React export for modern web design.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Framer',
    score: 8.8,
    ease: 7.5,
    design: 9.5,
    workflow: 'Direct design',
    price: '$15-35/mo',
    features: ['Best designs (9.5/10)', 'Code export', 'Smooth animations', 'Fast performance'],
    bestFor: 'Finished websites',
    strengths: ['Beautiful templates', 'Code export', 'Fast PageSpeed', 'Modern aesthetic'],
    weaknesses: ['Learning curve', 'Limited CMS', 'No native e-commerce', 'Less mature']
  },
  {
    name: 'Relume',
    score: 8.2,
    ease: 8.0,
    design: 8.5,
    workflow: 'Webflow Figma ‚Üí Webflow',
    price: '$20/mo + Webflow costs',
    features: ['Figma components', 'Webflow export', 'Component library', 'Design system'],
    bestFor: 'Webflow designers',
    strengths: ['Webflow integration', 'Component library', 'Figma workflow', 'Design system'],
    weaknesses: ['Requires Webflow', 'Figma learning', 'Additional cost', 'Not standalone']
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${comparisonData.title}: Which is Better?`} description={comparisonData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Relume or Framer better for website building?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer (8.8/10) offers better design quality (9.5/10 vs 8.5/10), is standalone, and includes code export. Relume (8.2/10) is a component library for Webflow that requires both Figma and Webflow subscriptions. Framer is better for quickly building finished websites with React export. Relume is better for Webflow designers who want a component-based workflow in Figma. If you use Webflow, Relume adds powerful component capabilities. If you want standalone design with code export, Framer is the better choice."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need Webflow to use Relume?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, Relume requires Webflow. Relume is a component library that exports to Webflow - it's not a standalone website builder. The workflow is: design in Relume's Figma kit ‚Üí export to Webflow ‚Üí customize and publish. You need both Relume subscription ($20/mo) AND Webflow subscription ($23+/mo). Framer is standalone at $15-35/mo with no additional requirements. If you're already invested in Webflow, Relume enhances your workflow. If you're starting fresh, Framer is simpler and cheaper."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export code from Relume or Framer?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer offers code export (React, HTML, CSS) on paid plans starting at $15/month. Relume exports to Webflow, which then offers its own code export on Webflow paid plans ($23+/month). So both ultimately support code export, but Framer is more direct. If you want React code directly, Framer is simpler. If you want Webflow expertise and then code export, the Relume ‚Üí Webflow ‚Üí export workflow works but costs more (Relume $20 + Webflow $23 = $43/month minimum)."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is faster: Relume or Framer?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer is faster for most projects because it's direct design in one platform. Relume requires three steps: design in Figma ‚Üí export to Webflow ‚Üí customize in Webflow. In testing, a marketing site took 6 hours in Framer vs 8 hours in Relume + Webflow. However, Relume can be faster for teams who reuse components repeatedly across multiple projects. The component library pays off at scale (10+ projects sharing components). For one-off sites, Framer wins on speed every time."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Relume worth the extra cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Relume costs $43+/month ($20 Relume + $23 Webflow) vs Framer at $15-35/month. That's $8-28/month more expensive. Relume is worth it ONLY if: (1) You're already committed to Webflow, (2) You have a team of 3+ designers who need consistency, (3) You build 10+ projects per year that can share components. If you're a solo freelancer building custom sites, Relume is overpriced. Framer gives you 90% of the value for half the cost. The component library only pays off at scale."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I use Relume without Figma?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, Relume requires Figma. The entire Relume workflow is built around Figma components. You design in Relume's Figma kit, then export to Webflow. If you don't know Figma, there's a learning curve before you can even use Relume. Framer has no such requirement - you design directly in Framer's interface. If you hate Figma or don't want to learn it, Framer is much more accessible. Relume is for Figma power users. Framer is for everyone else."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which has better templates: Relume or Framer?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer has better templates (9.5/10 design quality). Framer's templates are polished, modern, and ready to publish. Relume has good components (8.5/10) but they're building blocks, not finished templates. You assemble Relume components into your own design. If you want beautiful starting points, Framer wins. If you want complete control over every element and don't mind building from components, Relume works. Framer is for 'I want it to look great fast.' Relume is for 'I want to build exactly what I envision.'"
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50">
    <!-- Diagonal line pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F59E0B 0px, #F59E0B 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 md:py-24">
      <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#F59E0B] uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">COMPARISON</p>

      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-8">
        <span class="block">Relume Users Pay</span>
        <span class="block text-[#F59E0B] mt-2">$28/Month More</span>
        <span class="block mt-2">For Slower Work</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-gray-900">Framer (8.8/10):</strong> Standalone, $15-35/mo, best designs, direct workflow.<br class="hidden md:block" />
        <strong class="text-gray-900">Relume (8.2/10):</strong> Webflow add-on, $43+/mo, component library, needs Figma.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F59E0B] px-6 py-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase">Framer Design Quality</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#F59E0B]">9.5/10</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-6 py-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase">Relume Design Quality</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-700">8.5/10</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TESTING METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="bg-white border-b-[3px] border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Testing Methodology</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-gray-900">Real projects, not demos:</strong> Built the same 8-page marketing site in both tools. Measured time-to-publish, design quality, and final performance. Tested with solo freelancer (1 person) and Webflow agency team (5 people). Tracked actual workflow friction points. Cost analysis includes all required subscriptions. No affiliate commissions influence these ratings.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- Quick Answer -->
    <div class="bg-[#F59E0B] border-[3px] border-[#D97706] p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-white mb-4">Quick Answer</h2>
      <p class="text-white text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Framer wins for 80% of users.</strong> Standalone, better designs, cheaper, faster workflow.
      </p>
      <p class="text-white text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Relume wins for Webflow teams.</strong> Component library, design system, team consistency.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-2">
        <p class="text-white font-semibold">‚Üí Choose Framer if: You want standalone design with React export</p>
        <p class="text-white font-semibold">‚Üí Choose Relume if: You're a Webflow team needing components</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Score Comparison -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Score Breakdown</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {tools.map(tool => (
          <div class={`border-[3px] ${tool.name === 'Framer' ? 'border-[#F59E0B]' : 'border-gray-300'} bg-white p-8`}>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">{tool.name}</h3>
            <div class="text-6xl font-black text-[#F59E0B] mb-6">{tool.score}<span class="text-2xl text-gray-400">/10</span></div>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                <span class="text-gray-600 font-medium">Ease of Use</span>
                <span class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.ease}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                <span class="text-gray-600 font-medium">Design Quality</span>
                <span class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.design}/10</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t-[3px] border-gray-200">
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 uppercase font-bold mb-1">Workflow</p>
              <p class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900">{tool.workflow}</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 uppercase font-bold mb-1 mt-4">Price</p>
              <p class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.price}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature Table -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Feature Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse border-[3px] border-gray-300">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <th class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-left font-black">Feature</th>
              <th class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center font-black">Framer</th>
              <th class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center font-black">Relume</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Type</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Standalone builder</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Component library</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Design Quality</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Best (9.5/10)</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Very good (8.5/10)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Workflow</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Direct design</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Figma ‚Üí Webflow</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Code Export</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Built-in</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Via Webflow</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Requirements</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">None</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Figma + Webflow</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Component Library</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Basic</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Extensive</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Total Cost</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">$15-35/mo</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">$43+/mo</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE CASE STUDY -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">MY EXPERIENCE</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold mb-8">The $28/Month Design System Tax</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- THE BEFORE -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-orange-300 p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-orange-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE BEFORE</p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">"We build everything 2x faster with Relume."</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            That's what my Webflow designer friend told me. She swore by Relume's component library. "It's our design system. We never start from scratch. Everything is consistent."
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            She was already paying Webflow $23/month. Adding Relume at $20/month brought her to $43/month total. For comparison, I tested Framer at $15/month.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 bg-white border-[3px] border-orange-400 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-orange-900 font-bold">
              <span class="text-orange-600">Math:</span> $43 (Relume + Webflow) - $15 (Framer) = <span class="text-red-600">$28/month extra</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE PROBLEM</p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Three steps vs two steps</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Relume workflow:</strong> Design in Figma ‚Üí export to Webflow ‚Üí customize in Webflow ‚Üí publish.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Framer workflow:</strong> Design in Framer ‚Üí publish.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Relume adds an entire step. The Figma detour. Every change requires: update Figma ‚Üí re-export ‚Üí tweak Webflow. Framer: update and republish.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 bg-red-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-red-900 font-bold">
              <span class="text-red-600">The friction:</span> More steps = more time = more cost per project
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- THE TEST -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-50 to-teal-50 border-[3px] border-cyan-300 p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-cyan-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE TEST</p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Same site, different tools</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Project:</strong> 8-page marketing site. Hero, features, pricing, testimonials, FAQ, contact.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Framer:</strong> 6 hours from start to publish. Template customization, content swap, publish.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Relume + Webflow:</strong> 8 hours. Component selection in Figma, export, Webflow customization, CMS setup, publish.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 bg-white border-[3px] border-cyan-400 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-cyan-900 font-bold">
              <span class="text-cyan-600">Result:</span> Framer was <span class="text-green-600">33% faster</span> (6h vs 8h) for the same result
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- THE REALIZATION -->
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE REALIZATION</p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Then I tested with her team</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Her perspective changed when I watched her team work. 3 designers, all sharing the same Relume library. One person updates a button component ‚Üí everyone gets the update. Consistency across 20+ client projects.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">That's when it clicked:</strong> Relume isn't for individuals. It's for teams at scale.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-amber-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-4">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-amber-600 uppercase mb-2">Solo Freelancer</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Framer: 9.5/10 | Relume: 6/10</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-amber-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-4">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-amber-600 uppercase mb-2">5-Person Agency</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Framer: 7/10 | Relume: 9.5/10</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-gray-900 border-[3px] border-[#F59E0B] p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#F59E0B] uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">The 90-Day Breakdown</p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#F59E0B] mb-2">$28</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Extra monthly cost</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#F59E0B] mb-2">2h</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Saved per project (Framer)</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#F59E0B] mb-2">10+</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Projects to justify Relume</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#F59E0B] mb-2">3+</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Team members needed</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">THE HARD TRUTH</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">7 myths about Relume vs Framer that waste your money</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Myth #1: "Relume makes you faster"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-red-600">FALSE.</strong> Relume adds a step (Figma). For solo freelancers, Framer is 33% faster. Relume only pays off at scale (10+ projects sharing components). The "2x faster" claim assumes a team scenario most users don't have.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Myth #2: "Relume is a website builder"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-red-600">FALSE.</strong> Relume is a component library for Webflow. It cannot build anything without Webflow. The comparison isn't fair because they're different categories. Framer is standalone. Relume is an add-on.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Myth #3: "Framer has bad components"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-red-600">FALSE.</strong> Framer has solid components. They're just not as extensive as Relume's library. For 90% of projects, Framer's components are sufficient. Relume's 1000+ components only matter if you use them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Myth #4: "You need Figma for good design"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-red-600">FALSE.</strong> Framer's templates are better (9.5/10 vs 8.5/10). You can achieve excellent results without ever touching Figma. Figma is a skill investment. Framer is learnable in an afternoon.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Myth #5: "Relume code export is better"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-red-600">FALSE.</strong> Both export through Webflow. Framer exports React directly (more useful). Relume exports to Webflow, then Webflow exports. Framer is more direct if you want code.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Myth #6: "Component libraries are always better"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-red-600">FALSE.</strong> Component libraries shine when you reuse elements across 10+ projects. For one-off sites, they add overhead. Most freelancers build custom sites anyway. Components become constraints.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Myth #7: "Relume is only for Webflow power users"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-red-600">FALSE.</strong> Relume is for Webflow TEAMS. Solo Webflow users don't benefit enough to justify $20/month. The team consistency feature is Relume's real value. Without a team, you're paying for features you can't use.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

